#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#--[Record Structure Documentation]---------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=begin pod
=head1 Record N-TextIter

  unit class N-Object is repr('CPointer') is export;

To initialize just call C<new()> on it before use. For example;

  my Gnome::Gtk4::TextBuffer() $tb = $my-text-view-widget.get-buffer;
  my N-TextIter $t0 .= new;
  my N-TextIter $te .= new;
  $tb.get-bounds( $t0, $te);
  my Str $my-text = $tb.get-text( $t0, $te, False);

=end pod

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#--[Bitfields]------------------------------------------------------------------
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

=begin pod
=head1 Bitfields

=head2 GtkTextSearchFlags

Flags affecting how a search is done.

If neither %GTK_TEXT_SEARCH_VISIBLE_ONLY nor %GTK_TEXT_SEARCH_TEXT_ONLY are
enabled, the match must be exact; the special 0xFFFC character will match
embedded paintables or child widgets.

=item C<GTK_TEXT_SEARCH_VISIBLE_ONLY>; Search only visible data. A search match may
have invisible text interspersed.
=item C<GTK_TEXT_SEARCH_TEXT_ONLY>; Search only text. A match may have paintables or
child widgets mixed inside the matched range.
=item C<GTK_TEXT_SEARCH_CASE_INSENSITIVE>; The text will be matched regardless of
what case it is in.
=end pod

